-- Alesco to Buy Total Eden Holdings for A$250 Million
-- Robert Fenner
-- 2007-07-24T00:35:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2007-07-24/alesco-to-buy-total-eden-holdings-for-a-250-million-update1-.html

          
          
             Alesco Corp. (ALS) , an Australian building
materials and home products maker, agreed to buy Total Eden
Holdings Pty. for A$250 million ($221 million) in cash and stock
to expand into water management and irrigation systems.  
 Alesco will sell A$187.1 million of shares to help fund the
acquisition, the Sydney-based company said in a statement today.
Total Eden is currently owned by  AMP Ltd. (AMP) 's private equity arm.  
 The purchase will increase earnings-per-share by 3.6 percent
and give Alesco irrigation, waste and bore water businesses
serving agricultural and mining  customers  including BHP Billiton
Ltd.. Total Eden has annual sales of A$220 million across four
Australian states.  
 Alesco today said  net income  rose 2.6 percent to A$44
million, or 62.1 cents a share, in the year ended May 31 from
A$42.8 million, or 61.2 cents, a year earlier.  
 Shares in Alesco are halted from trading today. They closed
yesterday at A$13.96, valuing Alesco at A$994 million.  
